<title type="html"><![CDATA[Hardware tests]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=728&amp;p=6295#p6295"><![CDATA[
Most of the remaining aspects of the PPU have already been thoroughly examined using kevtris's "3-in-1 tester" (which tested lockout chip behavior, PPU I/O, and RGB palettes), such as sprite evaluation logic (by reading $2004) and VRAM address increment/reload times (down to the exact cycle). The only thing really left to figure out is exactly how color emphasis works (along with exactly how the palette is generated).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Sun Nov 06, 2005 12:23 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
